originalQuery: Which are the best budget dog food brands online?
submittedQuery: Which are the best budget dog food brands online?
response:

originalQuery: Which are the top healthy vegetarian dog biscuit brands available online?
submittedQuery: Which are the top healthy vegetarian dog biscuit brands available online?
response:
Here are some notable **healthy vegetarian (or vegan) dog biscuit brands** that are currently available online. These options are popular for their wholesome, plant-based ingredients and are generally well-regarded for their nutritional value, digestibility, and suitability for dogs with sensitivities.

---

###  Wild Earth Vegan Dog Treats  
- Made with koji protein, a nutrient-rich mushroom-based superfood providing all essential amino acids, plus omega fatty acids and prebiotics for gut health. These treats are also eco‑friendly, using significantly fewer resources than meat‑based alternatives. ([ecopetpathway.com](https://ecopetpathway.com/best-vegan-dog-treats-for-healthy-pets/?utm_source=openai))

- Crafted from organic, plant-based ingredients like oats, coconut, chia seeds, flaxseed, banana, and more. - Simple recipes (no more than eight ingredients per flavor) baked in the U.S., featuring plant protein from peanuts and peas. ([offthemrkt.com](https://www.offthemrkt.com/lifestyle/high-protein-vegan-dog-treats?utm_source=openai))

### Bright Planet Better Bac’n Bites  
- Soft, semi-moist vegan treats that mimic smoky bacon flavor using potatoes, peas, and beet juice. ([offthemrkt.com](https://www.offthemrkt.com/lifestyle/high-protein-vegan-dog-treats?utm_source=openai))

### Superfood Science Hypoallergenic Plant-Based Treats

- Oven-baked crunchy treats featuring fresh pumpkin and other fruits (e.g., apple, banana, blueberry) with a hint of cinnamon. - Certified vegetarian and organic, made with fruit- and veg-based recipes, and free from GMOs, preservatives, artificial colors, flavors, or sweeteners. ([dogrs.com](https://dogrs.com/11-best-vegetarian-andplant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai))

- Vegan jerky‑style treats made with pea protein, sweet potato, flaxseed, and no fillers. Free from animal products, these offer a protein-rich and allergen-friendly option. ([dogrs.com](https://dogrs.com/11-best-vegetarian-andplant-based-dog-treats/?utm_source=openai))
